The paper discusses the optimization of neural networks in the context of deep reinforcement learning, which is a subfield of machine learning. The focus is on policy gradient methods, which are commonly used in deep reinforcement learning. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.RO (Robotics). The paper also discusses the interplay between the dynamics of the environment and the algorithm properties, which suggests a connection to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
